.

Parts of the suture line are visible in several specimens. In specimen MB.C.30417.1 it shows the outline characteristic of the genus with a V-shaped external lobe with strongly diverging flanks, a very low lateral saddle, a deep E1 lobe and narrowly rounded E2 lobe. The ventrolateral saddle is almost symmetrical and broadly rounded, the lateral lobe is broadly rounded (
Fig. 6A
).
